column4: Oy vey G has himself a problem there...
@RF&P Can you carry paper to the printing works at (533, 37)?
Also, books to the shopping mall
he must be having a life today ;)
I did not see him yesterday either
Haha. I was having a life last night i.e not playing
@Y bahn, I need to leave for 15-30 mins, I'll work on that chain when I return
I will leave as well. Have to go to bed
Can you get rid of your depot at 597, 40?
if you reroute the road there try to build it with the public player
might be better to send it around 31 or 32
you can fiix up the blocks if you like
going to be building an underground freight yard; I hope it meets your high standards :)
i'm not sure i'm going to let the city expand there anyway
no, build it above ground to lock out the city growth if you can
i don't want these cities sprawling all over the map
It absoultely needs to be underground, not enough space
we can put the public road underground if necessary
you can't place it to the north east?
I am using a tunnel through the city
This will not be one of your giant freight yards, only mabye 4 tracks total if that
whatever suits you best, just saying not to put it underground on my account
as i like to see the traffic and want the city confined
let me look around a bit
i can destroy bits of city if you want a path
you don't want to destroy a double track through all of mascow
Okay, not Ideal, but I think I can do the yard above ground
you can put the line thru mascow above ground too
No, I will do a tunnel there.
i guess you have to cross your own line
i don't mind clearing a path at ground level
crossing your tramlines and a cow farm = hard
so long as trams and trains can co exist
or we can do it as a cutting
I don't think people want wet books and funiture
what if we put the public road on 26?
you have oermission to move the roads there anywhere you like with public
best if you pinch your lines together at 615,27
can you do the other two as well?
can you just leave those as is? the bridge will be long enough
just trying to make it tidier, that's all
well, either a little used road gets tidier or an important rail line gets messier
i'll build the road bridge, but pinching your lines there doesn't make them messier
won't make any difference, will still be 2 half bends
i think it's possible to build a junction to maintain the angle, let me experiment on some empty ground
or we can take the easy way out and move the road bridge south and put the kink in the road
still looks weird to me with the bridge not at the narrowest crossing
since it won't be long before some new industry shows up and changes everythingt
Yes, sometimes a bit odd but good.
We could put some up for east if you like
i thought it was very resourceful
he was asking for something to mark the boundary, he made his own arrangements :)
they won't work for us because they will face the wrong way
they would have to say "you are now leaving..."
Yes, "now leaving the east region, come back soon"
I seem to desync you every time I buy a train
